The national leadership of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has nullified the outcome of the party’s January 15, 2022 Ekiti state delegate congress. The party elected a three-member ad hoc ward delegate to elect the PDP flag bearer in the July governorship election. The national chairman of the PDP, Dr. Iyorchia Ayu, who announced the nullification at a media briefing on Monday night, said the Ekiti governorship primary election will be conducted using the statutory/automatic delegates list.   BREAKING: Abducted Bayelsa Commissioner regains freedom     UK scraps COVID-19 tests for fully vaccinated travellers…     Hanifa: Kano govt. revokes operational licences of all…   The primary election is billed to hold on Wednesday. The PDP chair called for the immediate withdrawal of all Court actions instituted by aggrieved parties in the dispute. - Advertisement - According to him, the decision of the party leadership was binding on all stakeholders in the Ekiti.